FBIS4-40230 "drsov115_m_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-115 Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 Tajikistan 2d Round of Peace Talks To Open 18 Jun in Tehran 2d Round of Peace Talks To Open 18 Jun in Tehran LD1506082394 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 0130 GMT 15 Jun 94 LD1506082394 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Text] The second round of Tajikistan's peace talks will commence on 18 June in Tehran. The office of the UN secretary general announced that the talks, which are aimed at achieving national reconciliation in Tajikistan, will be chaired by Ramero Piriz Ballon, an envoy of the secretary general. In addition to Tajik Government authorities and the government opposition groups, the representatives of the Islamic Republic of Iran, Russia, Pakistan, Afghanistan, Kazakhstan, Kyrgystan, Uzbekistan, and CSCE will attend the talks.
